        <updateDate>2006-11-28T17:35:40Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[Help and Opportunities for Parents of Exceptional Children Act of 2003 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow an annual  tax credit of up to $3,000 (with adjustments for inflation) per year for the qualified elementary or secondary education expenses of a dependent child with a disability.<p>Includes private, parochial, religious, or home schools among qualified educational institutions.]]></text>
      </summary>
